		<content type="html" xml:base="http://skysedge.us/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1488&amp;p=1587#p1587"><![CDATA[
Hi jw, good news: you can simulate a party line with Justine's 3G design without changing phone hardware, or re-configuring radios. There's a straightforward way plus the cell phone will still work as a cell phone... just in case.<br><br>This Raspberry Pi has been running Raspbx, a Private Branch Exchange in my home reliably for 2-3 years now. The data dongle on top is enabled for voice so one of the PBX extensions is a cell phone (useful for plans where cell to cell calls are free), details here: <a href="http://www.raspberry-asterisk.org" class="postlink">http://www.raspberry-asterisk.org</a>. The software runs on top of Asterisk: <em class="text-italics">"...the software behind most IP PBX systems, VoIP gateways, conference servers, used by SMBs, enterprises, call centers, carriers and governments worldwide."</em><br><br>You could program the Rotary Cellphone voicemail button to call the PBX which then simulates a party line. E.g. press a button (send tone) for line 2, setup a 3-way call, or "Direct Inward System Access" (DISA), where the Raspbx recognises your cell number and gives you full access. You don't even need to connect the PBX to a landline. It works best with a SIP provider. I have two SIP trunks programmed, one is Callcentric based in the US, the other is based in Europe. The possibilities are endless. Asterisk is to phone systems as Linux is to servers... oh and the PBX can be set to record all your calls if you wish (check if legal first).<br><br>[Justine: 2m? For real! I have a G8 call, I think it was issued in the late 70s, only active on 2m &amp; 70cm DMR though... in fact not really active period (just interested in the technology) 73s]<br><br>The Rotary Cellphone could be a very smart phone in <strong class="text-strong">disguise</strong>. Just like Tux here.<br><div class="inline-attachment"><dl class="file"><dt class="attach-image"><img src="http://skysedge.us/forum/download/file.php?id=29" class="postimage" alt="Raspbx.jpg" onclick="viewableArea(this);" /></dt></dl></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://skysedge.us/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1724">SteveC</a> — Mon Jun 01, 2020 9:34 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
