		<title type="html"><![CDATA[A New Function]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="http://skysedge.us/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1488&amp;p=1558#p1558"><![CDATA[
As most cell phones employ two transmitters, I wonder if it may be possible to add a Walkie Talkie (2-way or party line, UHF Radio) function to this dial-up cell phone as another unique anomaly....;--)<br>*In the old days of telephony, when individual lines in small communities were scarce, we used party lines so that everyone could be connected and we identified the person calling by the number of rings which prompted the targetted person to pick-up (example: 5-rings for Mary, 3-rings for Sam)<br>....there was no privacy here as anyone could listen-in but it still worked fine, just like a general open chat text message today.<br>__Am just thinking out-of-the-box here, as I believe this function does not exist in any other unit of the current smart phone variety.  <img class="smilies" src="http://skysedge.us/forum/images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" width="15" height="17" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green"><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://skysedge.us/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1744">13jwg</a> — Wed May 13, 2020 4:49 pm</p><hr />
